---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Media Kit — Brand Assets & Sponsorship"
  path="/media-kit/"
  description="Inlet Wire media kit. Brand statement, audience snapshot, logo pack, and sponsorship contact for BC-music-adjacent partners."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container" style="text-align: center;">
      <h1>Media kit</h1>
      <p class="lede" style="margin-inline: auto;">Brand statement, assets, and ways to work together.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="container prose stack-lg">
      <div>
        <h2>Brand statement</h2>
        <p>Inlet Wire is your direct line to BC artists. Each week, host Eric Chan sits down with an artist from the BC independent scene for a short, edited conversation — built to last past the release cycle and into the work itself.</p>
        <p>BC has a strong and active music scene. Most coverage is tied to quick promo, release-week attention, and short social clips. Inlet Wire is built for something longer lasting — a growing archive of BC artist stories that still feel meaningful after the single, the album, or the show has passed.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2>Assets</h2>
        <p>Logo pack (PNG + SVG, monochrome variants) available on request. Email <a class="link" href="mailto:contact@inletwire.com?subject=Media%20Kit">contact@inletwire.com</a> with "Media Kit" in the subject.</p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2>Sponsorship</h2>
        <p>Sponsoring Inlet Wire is not about buying ad space. It is about being connected to a growing local music platform built around artists, community, and thoughtful storytelling. The content is editorially independent — not shaped by PR, labels, or ad spend.</p>
        <p>To start a conversation, reach Eric at <a class="link" href="mailto:contact@inletwire.com">contact@inletwire.com</a>.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
